properties.diversions:
To get to Lismore from Queensland, take the Pacific Motorway until the Bangalow Road exit, then follow Bangalow Road.

The route to Lismore from the south is unchanged.

Take the Pacific Highway and Big River Way to Grafton, then Summerland Way to Cedar Point, then Bentley Road/Kyogle Road/Casino Street to Lismore.

To get to Casino and Grafton from the north, follow the route to Lismore, then take Casino Street/Kyogle Road/Bentley Road to Cedar Point, then Summerland Way.

To get to Casino and Grafton from the south, take the Pacific Highway and Big River Way to Grafton, then Summerland Way to Casino.

Access to Maclean is possible via the Pacific Motorway.

properties.diversions:
Heavy vehicles up to 26m GML B-doubles can use the following alternative routes:

  • Sydney/Newcastle to Brisbane via New England Hwy
  • Grafton to Brisbane via Gwydir Hwy, New England Hwy or Summerland Way
  • QLD/Far North Coast to Grafton via Lismore & Casino: exit the M1 at the Tintenbar interchange, then use Tamarind Dr, Tintenbar Rd and Teven Rd to Alstonville; then use Bruxner Hwy to Lismore; then use Casino St/Kyogle Rd/Bentley Rd to Cedar Point; then Summerland Way to Grafton (80km/h maximum speed; use UHF 29)
  • Grafton to QLD/Far North Coast via Casino & Lismore: Summerland Way to Cedar Point; then Bentley Rd/Kyogle Rd/Casino St to Lismore; then Bruxner Hwy to Alstonville; then Teven Rd, Tintenbar Rd and Tamarind Dr to rejoin the M1 at Tintenbar Interchange ((80km/h maximum speed; use UHF 29)
  • Local traffic to access Ballina via River St.
